    text: "Vienna Teng - Kansas\n\nBm             G\nSun sets in an ocean of\nD               A\nbrown farmland haze\nBm\nPower lines draped across\nG                 D          F#\nroads you could drive on for days\n           Em  F#m G   A\nWell, it's all too perfect\nEm   F#m G    A          Bm\nTime to  look back at us now\n\nG                      D       A\nEndless and empty like Kansas\n              Bm\nOur cities of clouds\nG                      D       A\nFlat on the table like Kansas\n\n  Bm         G\nI lay down in sheets\nD                  A\nsuddenly worn threadbare\n    Bm\nEvery wall I lean on\n     G                D\ntransforms to sliding doors\n         F#7\nand thin air\n        Em   F#m      G  A\nWell, I hope yours is kinder\n    Em    F#m         G    A\nLet go of this when you find her\n\n          Bm\nBury this hard\nG                          D    A\nDown underneath your white canvas\n              Bm\nOur houses of cards\nG                      D   A\nFlat on the table like Kansas\n\nEm\nIt's not regret\nA                Bm\nJust an unexpected accounting of debts\nBm\nOnly now called\nEm\nNo it's not regret\nA\nJust remembrance is all\nBm\nOf how close we had come\nBm\nThe war almost won\nA\nBut I sent up our flag and moved on\nBm\nYou and I\nG                       D     A\nLost to the winter like Kansas\nBm\nAnd all my goodbyes\nG                     D    A\nFlat on the table like Kansas",
