    text: "There are 2 different strumming methods for this song.\nThe first and easiest method is:\nDown, Up, Down, Up, Down, Up...\nthrough the whole song (Unless noted otherwise)\n\nSecond method which is:\nDown, Down, Up, Up, Down, Up, Down, Down, Up, Up...\nthrough the whole song (Unless noted otherwise)\n\n@ = Palm mute\n\nAm Am G G\nAm Am G G\n\n[Verse 1]\nAm                    C\n I want to live where soul meets body\nAm                        C\n And let the sun wrap its arms around me\n   Am                       C\nAnd  bathe my skin in water cool and cleansing\n    G                                Am\nAnd feel, feel what it’s like to be new\n\n                           C\nCause in my head there’s a greyhound station\nAm                            C\n  Where I send my thoughts to far off destinations\n   Am                         C\nSo they may have a chance of finding a place\n              G                      Am\nwhere they’re   far more suited than here\n\n(Am)        C       G            Am          C       G\nba-dup, ba-dup bap bah, ba-dup, bap buh, ba-dup bap bah\n        Am          F      G                Am\nba-dup, ba-dup  ba-dup bap bahhh-dup buddup bah\n\ne -------------------------------------------------------------------------\nB -------------------------------------------------------------------------\nG -------------------------------------------------------------------------\nD -------------------------------------------------------------------------\nA ---------------------------2--2--2--2--2--2--2--2------------------------\nE --5--5--0--0--1--1--3--3---3--3--3--3--3--3--3--3------------------------\n\nAm Am C C\nAm Am C C\n\n[Verse 2]\nAm                    C\n  I cannot guess what we’ll discover\nAm                                 C\n  When we turn the dirt with our palms cupped like shovels\n      Am                        C\nBut I know our filthy hands can wash one another’s\n    G                     Am\nAnd not one speck will remain\n\n(Am)   C            G\nI do believe it’s true\n               Am            C           G\nThat there are roads left in both of our shoes\n            Am            F\nBut if the silence takes you\n       G\nThen I hope it takes me too\n\ne -------------------------------------------------------------------------\nB -------------------------------------------------------------------------\nG -------------------------------------------------------------------------\nD -------------------------------------------------------------------------\nA ---------------------------2--2--2--2--2--2--2--2------------------------\nE --5--5--0--0--1--1--3--3---3--3--3--3--3--3--3--3------------------------\n\n   Am           C        G\nSo brown eyes I hold you near\n                 Am          C       G\nCause you’re the only song I want to hear\n       Am       F       G\nA melody softly soaring through my atmosphere\n\ne -------------------------------------------------------------------------\nB -------------------------------------------------------------------------\nG -------------------------------------------------------------------------\nD -------------------------------------------------------------------------\nA ---------------------------2--2--2--2--2--2--2--2------------------------\nE --5--5--0--0--1--1--3--3---3--3--3--3--3--3--3--3------------------------\n\n (Strum loudly)\n      Am         Am    C  Am   @   Am\nWhere soul meets body....\n      Am         Am    C\nWhere soul meets body....\n       G\nWhere soul meets body\n\n   Am       C          G\nAnd I do believe it’s true\n               Am            C           G\nThat there are roads left in both of our shoes\n       Am            F\nIf the silence takes you\n       G\nThen I hope it takes me too\n\ne -------------------------------------------------------------------------\nB -------------------------------------------------------------------------\nG -------------------------------------------------------------------------\nD -------------------------------------------------------------------------\nA ---------------------------2--2--2--2--2--2--2--2------------------------\nE --5--5--0--0--1--1--3--3---3--3--3--3--3--3--3--3------------------------\n\n   Am           C        G\nSo brown eyes I hold you near\n                 Am          C       G\nCause you’re the only song I want to hear\n      Am        F       G\nA melody softly soaring through my atmosphere\n\ne -------------------------------------------------------------------------\nB -------------------------------------------------------------------------\nG -------------------------------------------------------------------------\nD -------------------------------------------------------------------------\nA ---------------------------2--2--2--2--2--2--2--2------------------------\nE --5--5--0--0--1--1--3--3---3--3--3--3--3--3--3--3------------------------\n\n (Strum lightly)\n      Am        C       G\nA melody softly soaring through my atmosphere\n      Am        C       G\nA melody softly soaring through my atmosphere\n      Am        C       G\nA melody softly soaring through my atmosphere",
